{[%evp 0,13,28,30,4,13,28,18,19,19,30,21,21,21,21,21]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3.
d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Qf6 5. Nb3 (5. Be3 Bc5 {transposes to Main Line with 4...Bc5 5.
Be3, which we are avoiding as instead of 5.Be3 our repertoire recommends 5.Nb3.
}) (5. Nxc6 Bc5 {usually reached via 4...Bc5 when we play 5.Nb3.}) (5. Nb5 $5 {
is another critical try.} Bc5 6. Qe2 (6. Qd2 Bb6 7. N1c3 Nge7 8. Qf4 Qxf4 9.
Bxf4 d6 {shouldnot be problematic for Black.}) 6... Bb6 (6... Qd8 {has been
played as well and is a serious alternative.}) 7. N1c3 Nge7 8. Be3 Ba5 9. O-O-O
a6 10. Nd5 Nxd5 11. exd5 axb5 12. Bd4+ Qe7 13. dxc6 {has been seen in quite a
