10. c3 Bd6 $132) 9... Re8 $1 10. Nb5 (10. O-O-O d5 {is just great for Black as
in Hamrakulova-Sitnick, Bratislava 1993.}) 10... Nxe4 $1 11. O-O-O (11. Nxc7
Nd4 $1 12. Nxd4 Bxd2+ 13. Kd1 Nc3+ {and Black wins.}) 11... Bxd2+ 12. Nxd2 Nd6
$17 {and finally Black neutralizes the pressure on the e-file and c7 and
remains a big pawn up.}) (7. Be3 $6 {is too slow, in view of} d5 $1 {and now
after} 8. exd5 Nb4 $17 {[%csl Gb4,Rc2,Gg6] one of Black's key ideas in this
line has been shown.}) 7... Bb4+ (7... d5 {is a direct attempt to put White
