2015.}) 16... Qa5 17. Bd2 $1 Qa6 (17... Bb4 $2 18. a3 $1 Bxc3 19. Bxc3 Qa4 20.
Rb4 Qa6 {and only now} 21. Qxe5 $18) (17... Bd4 18. g4 $16) 18. Qxe5 d6 (18...
Bxf2 $2 19. c5 Qa5 20. Nb5 $18) 19. Qg5 $16 {Material is even, but Black is
poorly coordinated with such a queen on a6.}) 14. Rxa7 Qb4+ ({Worth checking is
} 14... Qe6 $5 15. Nd2 Bb4 16. O-O-O {and here an improvement should be found
for Black since} d5 $6 17. Nb3 $1 Kb8 18. Ra4 c5 19. Na5 Bxa5 20. Rxa5 dxc4 21.
Rxd8+ Rxd8 22. Qxc4 $16 {[%csl Rc5,Re5,Gf1,Gg5] is quite for Black as in
Cheparinov-Aravindh, Abu Dhabi 2018.}) 15. Nc3 Qb6 (15... d5 $5 {is probably
even more challenging.}) 16. Be3 Bc5 17. Bxc5 Qxc5 {and there is not much to
complain about. Black is doing fine in Darini-Sibashvili, Bandar e Anzali 2018}
